# {{.bundle_name}}

[Declarative Automation Bundle](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/dev-tools/bundles/) that deploys an sdp-meta pipeline (onboarding job + Lakeflow Declarative Pipelines) for layer `{{.layer}}`{{if eq .layer "bronze_silver"}} (pipeline_mode=`{{.pipeline_mode}}`){{end}}, source `{{.source_format}}`, onboarding file format `{{.onboarding_file_format}}`.

Generated by `databricks labs sdp-meta bundle-init`.

## Layout

```
{{.bundle_name}}/
├── databricks.yml                # bundle definition (dev + prod targets)
├── resources/
│   ├── variables.yml             # all configurable knobs
│   ├── sdp_meta_onboarding_job.yml   # python_wheel_task that writes dataflow specs
│   └── sdp_meta_pipelines.yml        # LDP pipelines + a job that runs them
├── notebooks/
│   └── init_sdp_meta_pipeline.py # runner notebook for each pipeline
├── recipes/                      # programmatic flow generators (read recipes/README.md)
│   ├── from_uc.py                # mirror N delta tables from a UC schema
│   ├── from_volume.py            # one cloudFiles flow per UC-volume subdirectory
│   ├── from_topics.py            # one kafka/eventhub flow per topic (10s or 100s)
│   └── from_inventory.py         # apply naming conventions to a hand-curated list
└── conf/
    ├── onboarding.{{if eq .onboarding_file_format "yaml"}}yml{{else}}json{{end}}          # flow definitions (edit me, or generate via recipes/)
    ├── samples/flows.csv         # example CSV for `bundle-add-flow --from-csv`
    ├── samples/topics.txt        # example topics list for `recipes/from_topics.py`
    {{- if or (eq .layer "silver") (eq .layer "bronze_silver")}}
    ├── silver_transformations.{{if eq .onboarding_file_format "yaml"}}yml{{else}}json{{end}}   # per-target SELECT projections
    {{- end}}
    └── dqe/example_table/bronze_expectations.{{if eq .onboarding_file_format "yaml"}}yml{{else}}json{{end}}
```

## Lifecycle

```bash
# 1. edit conf/onboarding.{{if eq .onboarding_file_format "yaml"}}yml{{else}}json{{end}} with your real sources and targets

# 2. deploy the bundle
databricks bundle deploy --target dev

# 3. run onboarding once (and again whenever you change the onboarding file)
databricks bundle run onboarding --target dev

# 4. run the pipelines (idempotent; Lakeflow will do incremental processing)
databricks bundle run pipelines --target dev
```

## Variables (see `resources/variables.yml`)

| Variable | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `uc_catalog_name` | UC catalog holding the sdp-meta schema and target schemas. |
| `sdp_meta_schema` | Schema for the `bronze_dataflowspec` / `silver_dataflowspec` tables. |
| `bronze_target_schema` | Schema for bronze LDP output tables. |
| `silver_target_schema` | Schema for silver LDP output tables. |
| `dataflow_group` | `data_flow_group` that ties flows in `conf/onboarding*` to this pipeline's `*.group`. |
| `sdp_meta_dependency` | PyPI coordinate or UC-volume wheel path used to install sdp-meta. |
| `serverless` | Run LDP pipelines serverless. |
| `development_enabled` | LDP pipeline `development` flag (overridden per target). |

## Installing sdp-meta on the pipelines

The job and both pipelines install sdp-meta from `${var.sdp_meta_dependency}`. Two options:

1. **PyPI** (when sdp-meta is published):
   ```yaml
   sdp_meta_dependency:
     default: databricks-labs-sdp-meta==0.0.11
   ```

2. **UC-volume wheel** (today, while sdp-meta isn't on PyPI):
   ```bash
   databricks labs sdp-meta bundle-prepare-wheel \
     --uc-catalog {{.uc_catalog_name}} \
     --uc-schema {{.sdp_meta_schema}} \
     --uc-volume sdp_meta_wheels
   ```
   Paste the printed `/Volumes/...` path into `resources/variables.yml` as the default for `sdp_meta_dependency`.

## Validating before deploy

```bash
databricks labs sdp-meta bundle-validate
```

Runs `databricks bundle validate` plus sdp-meta-specific checks: onboarding file exists, dataflow_group referenced by the pipelines is present in onboarding flows, and the configured `layer` matches which pipeline resources are deployed.

## Adding more flows

For one or two flows, edit `conf/onboarding.{{if eq .onboarding_file_format "yaml"}}yml{{else}}json{{end}}` directly, or run:

```bash
databricks labs sdp-meta bundle-add-flow            # interactive single flow
databricks labs sdp-meta bundle-add-flow --from-csv conf/samples/flows.csv
```

For tens or hundreds of flows, see `recipes/README.md` — three runnable
scripts that wrap the same engine and discover sources from UC, a UC volume,
or a hand-curated inventory.

